http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/Readers-Editor/corrections-and-clarifications/Corrections-and-Clarifications-December-10-2016/article13994138.ece

>> In an article, “An Ebola cloud with a silver lining,” (January 10, 2016) Dr. William Schaffner from Vanderbilt University Medical Centre in Nashville has been described as the first author of the paper. He is not the first author.>> In the last paragraph of a report, “CAT results: many score well in English” (January 9, 2016) S. Sri Ganesh has been quoted as saying, “Around 171 students have scored 98.5 percentile and 187 candidates have scored 99.3 percentile.” It should read as “171 is the score of the person in the 98.5th percentile and 187 is the score of the person in the 99.3th percentile.”